TITLE: Consumer sentiment in U.S. rises to highest level since July 2021
Consumer sentiment index jumps to 78.8 in early January from 69.7 in prior month
Existing-home sales fall 1% in December to 3.78 million
U.S. building permits rise 1.9% in December
Jobless claims drop 16,000 to 187,000 in Jan 13 week
Continuing U.S. jobless claims fall 26,000 to 1.81 million
Philly Fed factory index rises to negative 10.6 in January from negative 12.8 in prior month
U.S. housing starts fall 4.3% in December after revised 10.8% gain in November
U.S. business inventories dip 0.1% in November
Home builders sentiment index rises in January to 44 vs forecast of 39
